## 🛠 CLI Options

```
Usage: asa [OPTIONS] [PATH]

  Analyze the attack surface of your project before pushing to prod.

Options:
  --html FILE           Export HTML report to FILE
  --no-deps             Skip dependency CVE scan
  --no-configs          Skip misconfiguration scan
  --no-secrets          Skip hardcoded secrets scan
  --no-endpoints        Skip endpoint exposure scan
  --min-severity LEVEL  Minimum severity [low|medium|high|critical] (default: low)
  -q, --quiet           Only print summary
  --version             Show version and exit
  --help                Show this message and exit
```

---

## ⚙️ CI/CD Integration

ASA exits with code `1` if any HIGH or CRITICAL findings are found — making it easy to fail pipelines.

### GitHub Actions

```yaml
- name: Run ASA
  run: |
    pip install attack-surface-analyzer
    asa . --min-severity high --html asa-report.html

- name: Upload ASA report
  uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
  with:
    name: asa-security-report
    path: asa-report.html
```

### Pre-commit hook

```yaml
# .pre-commit-config.yaml
repos:
  - repo: local
    hooks:
      - id: asa
        name: Attack Surface Analyzer
        entry: asa
        args: [--min-severity, high, --no-endpoints]
        language: python
        pass_filenames: false
```

---

## 📦 Supported Ecosystems

| Manifest | Ecosystem | Version detection |
|---|---|---|
| `requirements.txt` / `requirements*.txt` | PyPI | ✅ Exact |
| `pyproject.toml` | PyPI | ✅ Exact |
| `Pipfile.lock` | PyPI | ✅ Exact |
| `package-lock.json` | npm | ✅ Exact |
| `package.json` | npm | ⚠️ Approximate |
| `go.mod` | Go | ✅ Exact |

---

## 🔒 Privacy

ASA never sends your source code anywhere. The only external call is a batch query to [OSV.dev](https://osv.dev/docs/) with **package names and versions only** — no file contents, no tokens, no paths.

